{
  "$comment": "c52 (D-FFI-MATH-INFINITY): ship INFINITY from <math.h> as a FLOAT constant. sqlite uses `(double)INFINITY` at runtime (sqlite3.c:37393/37423) -> S0001 INFINITY undeclared. The integer `constants` surface is integer-only (a float there fails loud F_ShippedLibUnsupportedType); a float-valued macro ships in `floatConstants` instead, injected as an f64-typed named constant whose HIR Ref folds to a +inf float literal. INFINITY is +inf on ALL targets (IEEE-754 f64), so no per-target variant; math.json gates no formats (available everywhere via the all-format `library` map).",
